<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
This species is characterized by non-ostiolate ascomata, 4-spored asci and very coarsely reticulate, citriform ascospores. These morphological features are also observed in 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium perplexum" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="perplexum">Microthecium perplexum</taxonomicName>
, but this species produces ascospores with only a third of the surface coarsely reticulate while the rest remains smooth-walled. 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium episphaerium" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="episphaerium">Microthecium episphaerium</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. retisporum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="retisporum">Mi. retisporum</taxonomicName>
differ from 
<taxonomicName genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. beatonii" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="beatonii">Mi. beatonii</taxonomicName>
in the production of 8-spored asci. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. retisporum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="retisporum">Mi. retisporum</taxonomicName>
produces a phialidic asexual morph and bulbils, which are absent in the other mentioned species, and smaller ascospores (17-20 
